and the last msg: 
```json
{
     "data": {
      "application/javascript": [
       "$('#img-video-1').attr('src', 'data:image/png;base64,......')"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"
      ]
},
```
- While others related to images must be not stored into _.ipynb_ file.


Btw, [my informal and immature solution now](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/10954), and the [Limit Output by _ConfigManager_](http://jupyter-contrib-nbextensions.readthedocs.io/en/latest/nbextensions/limit_output/readme.html) is not suitable here.

**Is there a better way to deal with it?**

